Preamble

The present research license is a non-exclusive, free, copyleft license (authorization for modification/distribution provided that future developments are subject to the same license) for software, specifically designed to ensure cooperation with the university community; it extends to software installed on servers. This License is intended solely for an academic user for exclusively Academic Research Use. This license is inspired by the INRIA academic license (license no. 5911).

The present license is specifically designed to ensure that, in all cases, including when the software is used on a server, the modified source code is accessible to the community. It requires the operator of a server to provide the source code of the modified version running on that server to the users of that server. Consequently, the public use of a modified version on a publicly accessible server provides access to the source code of the modified version.

This research license excludes any form of exploitation of the Program other than Academic Use. Other rights may be acquired by the licensee by contacting the department mentioned in Article 11 of the License.

