"License" refers to the present agreement.

"Copyright" also refers to copyright-like laws that apply to other types of works.

"The Program" refers to any work protected by copyright licensed under the present License.

"Academic Use" refers to research use performed by a public research laboratory. The object of the research may only concern the software covered by the License. Academic Use expressly excludes any lucrative or commercial activity, including, but not limited to, sale, licensing, manufacturing, or development of commercial products, use in the context of research funded by entities other than universities or research organizations, the provision of services and/or consulting, use in the context of research where an entity other than a university or research organization obtains rights to the research results or any other advantage, and use and/or exploitation for or on behalf of a public or private entity.

