The Parties are independent contracting parties. The Parties declare that the License can in no case be interpreted or considered as constituting a partnership, a group endowed with legal personality, nor a joint venture or a de facto company. Affectio societatis, the pursuit of sharing profits, and the contribution to losses are formally excluded.

19. Entire Agreement

The License, supplemented by the license files, expresses the entirety of the obligations of the Parties.

It cancels and replaces in their entirety all proposals, promises, commitments, discussions, and writings previously exchanged between the Parties on this same subject.

It supplements all agreements, contracts, and conventions previously signed between the Parties, it being understood that in case of contradiction, the provisions of the License shall prevail.

20. Partial Impossibility of Performance

If one or more clauses of the License cannot be put into effect for any reason whatsoever, the other provisions shall nevertheless retain their full validity. The Parties shall attempt, through good faith negotiations, to adapt or replace the clause(s) that proved to be inapplicable. The failure of the Parties to reach an agreement for the adaptation or replacement of the provisions in question shall not affect the validity of the License.

